# Simple-interest-
coding:
import java.util.Scanner;

public class SimpleInterestCalculator {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.print("Enter the Principal amount (P): ");
        double principal = scanner.nextDouble();
        System.out.print("Enter the Rate of Interest (R): ");
        double rate = scanner.nextDouble();
        System.out.print("Enter the Time (T in years): ");
        double time = scanner.nextDouble();
        double simpleInterest = (principal * rate * time) / 100;
        System.out.println("Simple Interest (SI): " + simpleInterest);
        scanner.close();
    }
}

output:
Enter the Principal amount (P): 5000
Enter the Rate of Interest (R): 5
Enter the Time (T in years): 2
Simple Interest (SI): 500.0
